title: Garden Done In Ice
author: sam
text: spireas arch in blending pattern under feathery snowfall glistening twigs in lifeless motion a world without a human soul and no emotion there at all imprisoned there until the thaw.   an alien world of crystal all daily movements cease in an almost deathly shimmer in the beauty of the peace the lovely garden i once saw imprisoned there until the thaw.   but in that desperate desolation of frigid plants i used to know in the land now deathly frozen a new bright realm begins to grow in dazzling beauty of flawless flaw living there until the thaw.   icicles hang like spanish moss grass like glass crunches under my foot.  snow covers all in a fluffy frost crystal on every leaf or root.  a world without life's normal laws,   living there until the thaw.   snow lies around in the cold's sharp slice in the garden,  done in ice.

title: Poetry
author: sara
text: poetry  poetry is beautiful,   it's everything,   anything,  it can cure your thirst,  of knowledge,  the grace of the words written so eloquently on the page,  is grace of an observing poet.    anyone,  can call them,  poets,  but alas,  not everyone,  are so fluent in the language,  of verses and rhyme joined together.     poetry is like a cookie,  when you start it,   you are apprehensive,  what if it doesn't taste good? what if its tasteless? what if it's the wrong flavor? push away those fears.   poetry can cure your sour day,  sing a song in your happiness,  paint a sky pale pink,  with an artists hand,  steadily weave your way,  into triumph of,   powerful words woven into verses,  like a spiders web.
